<h1>Fitness</h1>

<p>There a several aspects to your fitness that you can improve and maintain to make yourself a better rugby player.</p>

<h3>Physical aspects</h3>

<h5>Stamina</h5>

<p>This is most important for players in any position. In an 80 minute match, players will run 5-8km, depending on their position. A back will make approximately 120 impacts and a forward will make ~300. On top of all this, they will need to push, pull, lift, sprint, kick, grip, jump, roll, dive and immediately return to their feet every time.</p>

<p>You could be one of the most skilful players in the world, but you won't be selected if you can't maintain a strong standard of play for a full match.</p>

<p>Go running. You should be able to complete a 5km run in under 30 minutes. You may also train and test your stamina using the bleep test. There are several smartphone apps for bleeps tests.</p>

